{
  "texts": [
    "(P12).In contrast to making a preliminary visualization for quick exploration, \"getting the final version is hard\" (P4).",
    "What made this task challenging for some participants was their \"lacking of an eye for aesthetics\" (P4, P18), often referring to having difficulty with making sensible color choices.",
    "Other challenging customization tasks were alignment or composition adjustments or deciding how additional annotation information has to be shown without compromising other parts.",
    "Some felt like they were unable to do \"self-feedback\", or found tools not supportive of making expressive edits, therefore \"sticking to the basics\" (P18).",
    "Often, participants used Adobe Illustrator as a way to create more expressive visualizations, but they experienced efficiency and learnability barriers: \"I have to adjust everything in Adobe Illustrator again."
  ]
}